WEBVTT

00:00:46.160 --> 00:00:51.370
For you, billions and billions of heartbeats

00:00:51.370 --> 00:00:58.040
are nothing at all; just the blink of an eye

00:00:58.040 --> 00:01:03.290
Although I'm trapped by
the past and lament the future

00:01:03.290 --> 00:01:09.200
inevitability won't allow for
even a speck of a miscalculation

00:01:09.200 --> 00:01:15.330
Our dreams and futures that
form and expand into "infinity"

00:01:15.330 --> 00:01:21.160
allow us the right to be vain,

00:01:21.160 --> 00:01:27.370
while the two hands
point out what is "finite"

00:01:27.370 --> 00:01:31.950
All of which leads to a cruel
contract and choice to make

00:01:31.950 --> 00:01:34.200
Hacking to the Gate

00:01:34.200 --> 00:01:41.120
So, now, with each passing
second, I'll cross world lines

00:01:41.120 --> 00:01:46.080
to protect that smile on your face

00:01:46.080 --> 00:01:53.080
Then, once again, into a
time loop without sadness

00:01:53.080 --> 00:01:59.750
I will be swallowed up as a lone observer

00:02:18.500 --> 00:02:21.500
I'm starving...

00:02:26.660 --> 00:02:30.120
-Are you going to Comima--
-You're going again tomorrow, aren't you?

00:02:30.120 --> 00:02:31.120
Huh?

00:02:31.120 --> 00:02:32.120
Yeah...

00:02:32.120 --> 00:02:35.370
-Will you be back around this time?
-I think so.

00:02:37.200 --> 00:02:39.330
Say! You should come with me, Kurisu-chan!

00:02:39.330 --> 00:02:41.790
Crowded places aren't really my thing...

00:02:41.790 --> 00:02:44.290
It shouldn't be too crowded on the second day!

00:02:44.290 --> 00:02:46.790
You should come too, Okarin--

00:02:53.290 --> 00:02:55.200
Come with me, Okabe!

00:02:58.200 --> 00:03:01.790
What's with you?! You've been
moody ever since you got back!

00:03:01.790 --> 00:03:05.540
Can't you tell Mayuri's trying to cheer you up?!

00:03:05.540 --> 00:03:07.120
I know she is.

00:03:07.120 --> 00:03:10.000
But I can't just stay calm!

00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:11.120
Huh?

00:03:11.120 --> 00:03:13.580
It happens tomorrow!

00:03:14.370 --> 00:03:17.500
Even if she's fine today, tomorrow she'll be...!

00:03:21.160 --> 00:03:24.370
How many times have
I explained this to you now?

00:03:25.910 --> 00:03:27.540
Okabe?

00:03:30.620 --> 00:03:32.830
There's something I have to tell you.

00:03:41.790 --> 00:03:45.410
Mayuri does?! Tomorrow?!

00:03:45.410 --> 00:03:47.620
She'll most likely end up dead.

00:03:47.620 --> 00:03:50.500
At first, it'd happen on
the night of Friday the 13th.

00:03:50.500 --> 00:03:56.250
But each D-mail I undid
pushed it back one day.

00:03:58.450 --> 00:04:01.330
Tomorrow, I'll go with her to Comima.

00:04:01.330 --> 00:04:03.500
Is there a way to save her?!

00:04:06.370 --> 00:04:09.700
-I'm going to watch her die.
-What?!

00:04:09.700 --> 00:04:13.950
I need to determine her
precise deadline on this world line.

00:04:13.950 --> 00:04:18.540
And then I'll time leap again.

00:04:18.540 --> 00:04:20.580
There's no other way.

00:04:24.750 --> 00:04:29.450
So the next D-mail to undo is the
one by this "Kiryu Moeka" person?

00:04:29.450 --> 00:04:32.330
Yeah. I even know what it said.

00:04:32.330 --> 00:04:36.830
She kept her past self
from switching cell phones.

00:04:36.830 --> 00:04:39.830
We'll need to send a message
from her phone this time.

00:04:39.830 --> 00:04:42.290
You go look for her!

00:04:45.700 --> 00:04:48.000
I'll go with Mayuri to Comima!

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:48.950
Are you...?!

00:04:48.950 --> 00:04:52.040
If we're lucky, maybe Mayuri won't--

00:04:52.040 --> 00:04:54.250
Maybe I can keep it from happening!

00:04:54.250 --> 00:04:55.620
Do you know what you're saying?!

00:04:55.620 --> 00:04:58.000
If I don't find Moeka, then it'll mean--!

00:04:58.000 --> 00:05:00.200
I'll contact you immediately!

00:05:01.910 --> 00:05:05.580
Also, you can talk to me
about anything, you know.

00:05:05.580 --> 00:05:10.580
If you need help, for
anything at all, I'm there for you.

00:05:10.580 --> 00:05:13.700
Yeah... You always have been.

00:05:15.370 --> 00:05:17.580
Never forget.

00:05:17.580 --> 00:05:21.160
Whatever world line
you're on, you aren't alone.

00:05:21.160 --> 00:05:22.700
I'm there for you!

00:05:31.870 --> 00:05:33.540
"At Ariake now.

00:05:33.540 --> 00:05:36.410
Huge crowd here, worse than I imagined.

00:05:36.410 --> 00:05:38.250
Save me..."

00:05:41.200 --> 00:05:44.620
"No reply from Moeka,
but I found where she works.

00:05:46.250 --> 00:05:48.200
I'll check with them."

00:05:49.290 --> 00:05:51.580
"Roger. Don't do anything crazy."

00:05:54.160 --> 00:05:56.080
Kiryu Moeka?

00:05:56.080 --> 00:06:00.540
Ah, I think I remember her.
She worked for a couple days and then quit.

00:06:00.540 --> 00:06:01.790
Her address?

00:06:01.790 --> 00:06:04.660
I have it... but who exactly are you?

00:06:11.870 --> 00:06:12.830
"Heights White"

00:06:14.450 --> 00:06:15.620
"Heights White 202
Kiryu Moeka"

00:06:20.540 --> 00:06:21.580
Understood.

00:06:21.580 --> 00:06:23.040
Excuse me...!

00:06:24.620 --> 00:06:28.410
Kiryu Moeka... committed suicide?

00:06:28.410 --> 00:06:30.500
-You're certain of it?
-Yeah.

00:06:30.500 --> 00:06:32.700
-When did it happen?!
-Last night.

00:06:32.700 --> 00:06:35.660
They took her body to Third Chiyoda Hospital.

00:06:35.660 --> 00:06:37.040
We were at a real loss, though.

00:06:37.040 --> 00:06:39.870
-This can't be...
-Couldn't find any relatives to contact.

00:06:43.410 --> 00:06:44.910
Hey, are you okay?

00:06:44.910 --> 00:06:47.410
Suicide?

00:06:47.410 --> 00:06:49.080
Why?

00:06:53.160 --> 00:06:55.500
Did one of her partners kill her?

00:06:55.500 --> 00:06:58.330
Before killing Mayuri?

00:06:58.330 --> 00:07:00.750
But...

00:07:00.750 --> 00:07:02.620
It doesn't matter why!

00:07:02.620 --> 00:07:05.830
Mayuri's still gonna be...!

00:07:07.750 --> 00:07:09.120
A time leap!

00:07:09.120 --> 00:07:11.750
If I time leap to before Moeka dies...!

00:07:30.540 --> 00:07:33.660
-Hello?
-O-Okabe...!

00:07:33.660 --> 00:07:35.950
Sh-She's dead... Mayuri's...

00:07:35.950 --> 00:07:37.410
Mayuri's...

00:07:37.410 --> 00:07:41.870
-The deadline is 7:52 pm...
-Mayuri!

00:07:41.870 --> 00:07:43.870
I'm sorry.

00:07:47.830 --> 00:07:48.830
Huh?!

00:07:48.830 --> 00:07:51.330
Okabe! Did you eat this?!

00:07:51.330 --> 00:07:55.700
Look right here! It clearly
has "Makise" written on it!

00:07:56.330 --> 00:07:58.080
Hey! Are you listening to me?!

00:07:58.080 --> 00:08:01.580
Never forget. You aren't alone.

00:08:02.620 --> 00:08:05.870
Yes. You're right, Kurisu.

00:08:05.870 --> 00:08:09.290
Huh?! Wh-What did you just say?

00:08:09.290 --> 00:08:11.620
Do you know a girl named Kiryu Moeka?

00:08:11.620 --> 00:08:13.830
Huh? Who?

00:08:13.830 --> 00:08:16.500
I just did a time leap.

00:08:18.250 --> 00:08:20.000
What do you mean?

00:08:23.870 --> 00:08:25.120
"Heights White"

00:08:57.830 --> 00:08:59.200
FB...

00:08:59.950 --> 00:09:04.620
FB... FB...

00:09:04.620 --> 00:09:06.290
Answer me...

00:09:06.290 --> 00:09:08.040
Please...

00:09:08.040 --> 00:09:09.580
FB...

00:09:09.580 --> 00:09:13.870
Why won't you message me?

00:09:13.870 --> 00:09:17.500
Please... Reply to me...!

00:09:17.500 --> 00:09:19.620
FB...

00:09:21.250 --> 00:09:22.830
Kiryu Moeka...

00:09:22.830 --> 00:09:26.910
-I did everything you asked me to do...
-It's me, Okabe!

00:09:26.910 --> 00:09:29.620
Give me orders, FB!

00:09:29.620 --> 00:09:32.080
Can't you hear me?! Hey!

00:09:32.370 --> 00:09:35.160
FB... FB...

00:09:35.950 --> 00:09:37.040
FB...

00:09:38.000 --> 00:09:41.290
FB... FB...

00:09:43.870 --> 00:09:46.200
N-No! No!

00:09:46.200 --> 00:09:49.290
No! No...!

00:10:04.160 --> 00:10:06.290
I'll never forgive her!

00:10:06.290 --> 00:10:09.910
Never...!

00:10:18.120 --> 00:10:19.700
Give it back...

00:10:22.330 --> 00:10:26.370
Give it back! Give it back!

00:10:26.370 --> 00:10:27.330
Give it back!

00:10:27.330 --> 00:10:28.200
"Okabe Rintarou"

00:10:28.580 --> 00:10:32.250
-It's me! You have her phone?!
-Just stole it! Get the D-mail set to go!

00:10:32.250 --> 00:10:33.540
It's ready!

00:10:33.540 --> 00:10:37.040
-What's that sound?
-Never mind that! Where's Mayuri?!

00:10:37.040 --> 00:10:40.290
The CRT Workshop. The 42-inch TV's on!

00:10:40.290 --> 00:10:41.750
All right!

00:10:43.200 --> 00:10:44.160
Kurisu!

00:10:44.160 --> 00:10:45.290
"Get new phone before they sell out"
Activate it!

00:10:45.290 --> 00:10:46.120
"Get new phone before they sell out"
Right!

00:10:46.120 --> 00:10:46.950
Right!

00:10:47.910 --> 00:10:49.250
Give it back! Give it back!

00:10:49.250 --> 00:10:52.160
This is the last one.

00:10:52.160 --> 00:10:54.830
Once I send this...

00:10:54.830 --> 00:10:56.250
...Mayuri will be...!

00:11:13.160 --> 00:11:15.450
Give it back! Give it back!

00:11:15.450 --> 00:11:17.250
Give back my phone!

00:11:17.250 --> 00:11:19.790
-Huh? Nothing's happened!
-Give it back!

00:11:19.790 --> 00:11:21.330
-What's going on?!
-Did you send it?!

00:11:21.330 --> 00:11:23.700
Yes! Did you activate it right?!

00:11:23.700 --> 00:11:26.040
The discharge took place! What's happened?!

00:11:26.040 --> 00:11:28.040
My Reading Steiner hasn't kicked in!

00:11:28.040 --> 00:11:29.620
Huh?!

00:11:29.620 --> 00:11:32.620
My Reading Steiner hasn't activated...

00:11:32.620 --> 00:11:34.620
How can this be?

00:11:37.830 --> 00:11:42.700
-Give it back! Give it back!
-Geez, what are you doing in there?

00:11:44.540 --> 00:11:47.830
Give it back! Give it back! Give it back!

00:11:47.830 --> 00:11:49.290
It's not working!

00:11:49.290 --> 00:11:53.290
A D-mail's effects greatly depend
on the person who receives it!

00:11:53.290 --> 00:11:57.250
Could it be that your message
wasn't enough to change her actions?!

00:11:57.250 --> 00:11:59.580
What do we do, then?!

00:12:07.080 --> 00:12:08.700
It didn't change!

00:12:08.700 --> 00:12:11.370
She didn't change her cell phone!

00:12:11.370 --> 00:12:14.450
What do you mean?! Are you sure?!

00:12:14.450 --> 00:12:17.870
"I got a new phone four days ago,

00:12:17.870 --> 00:12:21.450
but I wanna tell myself not to buy it."

00:12:21.450 --> 00:12:24.290
She must've sent a different
message at the last second!

00:12:24.290 --> 00:12:27.500
What! So we don't
know what her D-mail said?!

00:12:27.500 --> 00:12:29.910
There should be a record of it in here!

00:12:29.910 --> 00:12:31.830
I'll check--

00:12:34.410 --> 00:12:37.790
Give it back! Give it back!

00:12:37.790 --> 00:12:41.120
-What's going on?! Okabe! Okabe!
-Give it back!

00:12:41.120 --> 00:12:43.290
I'll call you back!

00:12:43.290 --> 00:12:46.410
Give it back! Give it back!

00:12:46.410 --> 00:12:48.200
Give it back!

00:12:49.000 --> 00:12:52.370
Give it back! Give it back!

00:12:57.120 --> 00:13:00.620
Come on! What are you doing in there?!

00:13:01.450 --> 00:13:03.080
Give it back...

00:13:03.080 --> 00:13:05.750
Okabe!

00:13:12.580 --> 00:13:15.200
Give it back! Give it back!

00:13:28.450 --> 00:13:31.580
Sheesh! What is going on in there?

00:13:37.160 --> 00:13:38.790
Hey, you...

00:13:43.580 --> 00:13:48.620
Sheesh, couples these days can be so scary...

00:14:07.160 --> 00:14:10.540
What can I do...

00:14:10.540 --> 00:14:15.080
What can I do... to make you give it back?

00:14:15.080 --> 00:14:18.540
Do you remember sending a D-mail?

00:14:18.540 --> 00:14:21.620
A D-what...?

00:14:21.620 --> 00:14:25.330
You should've received a
strange e-mail two weeks ago.

00:14:25.330 --> 00:14:28.080
From your future self.

00:14:28.080 --> 00:14:29.700
How do you...?

00:14:29.700 --> 00:14:33.620
Tell me what it said!
And then you can have it back!

00:14:33.620 --> 00:14:36.330
What's the matter?! Can't tell me?!

00:14:37.700 --> 00:14:42.080
Was it about the IBN 5100... or the Rounders?!

00:14:42.080 --> 00:14:43.160
Oh, am I right?!

00:14:43.160 --> 00:14:45.910
Tell me! What did the message say?!

00:14:47.540 --> 00:14:49.410
Don't you want your phone back?!

00:14:49.410 --> 00:14:51.750
-I can't betray--
-Betray who?!

00:14:54.200 --> 00:14:56.540
This "FB" of yours?

00:14:56.540 --> 00:15:01.080
My orders come from FB.

00:15:01.080 --> 00:15:04.790
FB is everything to me...

00:15:04.790 --> 00:15:07.830
So this person's calling the shots?!

00:15:10.160 --> 00:15:14.200
You can't betray FB? How nice and loyal of you.

00:15:14.200 --> 00:15:19.700
But this FB of yours doesn't
seem to give a damn about you!

00:15:20.160 --> 00:15:23.500
FB has abandoned you for good!

00:15:23.500 --> 00:15:25.870
That's not true...!

00:15:25.870 --> 00:15:29.410
You've lost all contact, right?!
You've been betrayed!

00:15:29.410 --> 00:15:31.750
-You've been tossed aside!
-You're wrong!

00:15:31.750 --> 00:15:34.580
FB isn't like that!

00:15:41.700 --> 00:15:43.330
FB saved me...

00:15:43.330 --> 00:15:45.790
"...the Cabinet Office..."
FB saved me...

00:15:47.370 --> 00:15:50.620
No, you were used!

00:16:11.160 --> 00:16:15.450
Do you know how I know that?!

00:16:16.120 --> 00:16:19.870
FB is like a mother to me...

00:16:19.870 --> 00:16:22.200
"What sort of work would I have to do?"

00:16:22.200 --> 00:16:25.160
I have a type of time machine.

00:16:25.160 --> 00:16:27.160
The e-mail from the future is proof!

00:16:27.160 --> 00:16:28.790
"Even work I could do?"

00:16:28.790 --> 00:16:30.000
"Yes, there's nothing to worry about."

00:16:30.000 --> 00:16:33.200
FB... made me feel needed...

00:16:33.200 --> 00:16:37.870
"I've never had a job before.
I don't have any skills, either."

00:16:49.700 --> 00:16:52.200
I've seen what happens!

00:16:52.200 --> 00:16:53.950
You...

00:16:54.540 --> 00:16:56.370
You...

00:16:59.870 --> 00:17:04.080
In four days, you commit
suicide in this very room.

00:17:05.330 --> 00:17:07.830
You keep waiting to hear from FB...

00:17:07.830 --> 00:17:10.660
...until you die all alone in this room!

00:17:10.660 --> 00:17:13.000
-You're lying.
-It's the truth!

00:17:13.000 --> 00:17:15.870
You'll never hear from FB again!

00:17:15.870 --> 00:17:18.450
You've been abandoned!

00:17:18.450 --> 00:17:19.290
You're lying...

00:17:19.290 --> 00:17:22.080
When's the last time FB responded?! Huh?!

00:17:22.080 --> 00:17:26.040
You've been waiting all this time,
haven't you?! Odd, don't you think?!

00:17:28.830 --> 00:17:31.160
You're going to die here!

00:17:31.160 --> 00:17:32.250
No...

00:17:32.250 --> 00:17:34.410
In this dark, empty room...

00:17:34.410 --> 00:17:35.330
No...

00:17:35.330 --> 00:17:38.000
...you, Mayuri's killer...

00:17:38.000 --> 00:17:41.950
...all alone, abandoned, and
betrayed, like a piece of garbage...

00:17:41.950 --> 00:17:43.750
-No...
-...end your life!

00:17:43.750 --> 00:17:45.910
No one comes to help you!

00:17:45.910 --> 00:17:47.830
Not even FB!

00:17:48.500 --> 00:17:53.790
No!

00:18:28.290 --> 00:18:30.160
I'm sorry...

00:18:33.330 --> 00:18:36.200
You said FB's like a mother.

00:18:36.200 --> 00:18:38.410
Is FB a woman?

00:18:39.700 --> 00:18:41.120
I think so.

00:18:41.120 --> 00:18:42.700
You "think"?

00:18:42.700 --> 00:18:45.160
We've never met...

00:18:45.160 --> 00:18:47.080
I never want to...

00:18:48.580 --> 00:18:53.700
I'm sure she'd hate me if we did...

00:18:53.700 --> 00:18:56.790
Sounds like you've never
even talked on the phone.

00:18:56.790 --> 00:18:58.910
How could you take orders
from someone like that?!

00:18:58.910 --> 00:19:01.910
She gave me a place where I belong...

00:19:01.910 --> 00:19:04.160
A place where you belong?

00:19:10.870 --> 00:19:14.330
You're a fool!

00:19:17.080 --> 00:19:18.620
"The retro PC is stored
at Yanabayashi Shrine."

00:19:18.620 --> 00:19:20.080
"Procure at once."

00:19:20.450 --> 00:19:22.500
Okabe?!

00:19:25.160 --> 00:19:26.620
Don't worry me like that!

00:19:26.620 --> 00:19:29.200
You... were worried about me?

00:19:29.200 --> 00:19:31.200
N-No!

00:19:31.200 --> 00:19:32.910
I'm sorry.

00:19:32.910 --> 00:19:34.370
So?

00:19:35.620 --> 00:19:39.160
So the IBN 5100 was stolen by...

00:19:39.160 --> 00:19:40.160
By Moeka.

00:19:40.160 --> 00:19:42.410
Where is it now?!

00:19:42.410 --> 00:19:44.870
That's all I've got.

00:19:44.870 --> 00:19:47.040
We'll undo the D-mail as planned.

00:19:47.040 --> 00:19:51.330
Got it. Approximately 11:00 am on July 31st.

00:19:54.250 --> 00:19:59.750
"Shrine is a trap. Don't go. It's not there!"

00:19:59.750 --> 00:20:01.580
It's activated!

00:20:03.540 --> 00:20:05.950
This should do it...

00:20:18.620 --> 00:20:19.950
Why?!

00:20:19.950 --> 00:20:22.700
-Well?!
-It didn't work!

00:20:24.370 --> 00:20:28.000
Did the Kiryu Moeka in the
past not believe the D-mail?

00:20:28.000 --> 00:20:31.290
Maybe she believed the
first one, just to be safe?!

00:20:31.290 --> 00:20:34.250
Let's send another, different message!

00:20:34.250 --> 00:20:35.910
No...

00:20:35.910 --> 00:20:39.540
I think there's only
one person she'll listen to.

00:20:39.540 --> 00:20:43.870
If we can send a message from her
phone, Moeka will obey without question!

00:20:43.870 --> 00:20:45.870
Huh? Who are you talking about?

00:20:53.120 --> 00:20:56.040
I'm going to look for FB.

00:20:56.040 --> 00:20:58.870
Any idea where she might be?

00:20:58.870 --> 00:21:00.660
I guess you wouldn't tell me anyway.

00:21:00.660 --> 00:21:04.950
Earlier... You said I killed someone...

00:21:04.950 --> 00:21:06.200
Is that in the future?

00:21:06.200 --> 00:21:10.040
Yeah. You'd kill if FB ordered you to, right?

00:21:10.790 --> 00:21:12.870
I would.

00:21:12.870 --> 00:21:15.830
Even if you knew you were being used?!

00:21:17.950 --> 00:21:22.750
That's how you die! Completely
dependent but abandoned!

00:21:22.750 --> 00:21:25.410
In four days, on August 15!

00:21:25.410 --> 00:21:30.750
The world has set your death
in stone! There's no escaping it!

00:21:30.750 --> 00:21:34.410
But I refuse to accept that!

00:21:34.410 --> 00:21:37.660
I'm going to fight the world!

00:21:37.660 --> 00:21:41.750
I will save Mayuri!

00:21:55.750 --> 00:21:57.870
The coin locker...

00:22:00.870 --> 00:22:02.790
In front of the Dai Building...

00:22:04.250 --> 00:22:06.910
The IBN 5100...

00:22:20.660 --> 00:22:23.830
With my vision restricted,

00:22:23.830 --> 00:22:29.620
there's no escape

00:22:29.620 --> 00:22:32.660
from the merciless control

00:22:32.660 --> 00:22:37.370
of the twelve

00:22:37.370 --> 00:22:41.370
Wishing for

00:22:41.370 --> 00:22:46.250
a tomorrow of repose,

00:22:46.250 --> 00:22:50.410
I embark for the horizon

00:22:50.410 --> 00:22:54.870
of the sacred phenomenon in my hand

00:22:54.870 --> 00:22:59.160
Trapped by the covenant

00:22:59.160 --> 00:23:03.450
and shown the outline of false evidence

00:23:03.450 --> 00:23:07.750
the heaven and earth

00:23:07.750 --> 00:23:12.700
of life lets time blindly flow by

00:23:12.700 --> 00:23:18.040
Flutter, butterfly, oh, miraculous butterfly!

00:23:18.040 --> 00:23:21.580
I give myself to you

00:23:21.580 --> 00:23:26.000
Oh, butterfly of tears, dazzling butterfly!

00:23:26.000 --> 00:23:28.750
It's all...

00:23:28.750 --> 00:23:33.660
...about to be rewritten now

